text:
Bird strike forces Jet2 flight to land at Manchester Airport Published on : Friday, September 18, 2015
Jet2 flight with 144 passengers on board makes an emergency landing at Manchester Airport after a reported bird strike.
As per the reports from local news agencies and eye witnesses, smoke and flames from the plane were spotted. A booming noise was heard as the aircraft passed over the Old Trafford cricket ground on Thursday at about 2pm.
The Jet2 flight was scheduled fly from Manchester to Barcelona. According to another witness, who spotted the flight flying over Northwich in Cheshire said that there was a ghastly sound while the plane flew very low over his office and was trying to go higher. The plane was reportedly back firing along with a very loud sound.
The flight landed safely at the Manchester Airport there were no injuries as per the latest reports.
